    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith `vim.opt.cmdheight = 0`, the command-line should replace the statusline when entering command mode, reusing the same screen line. However, when ui2 is enabled, the statusline remains visible and moves 1 line up.\n\n<img width=\"691\" height=\"211\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d8ba1778-4ad8-4344-88b8-2647768a9336\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nwith: `vim.opt.cmdheight = 0`\nadding:\n```lua\nvim.g.loaded_ui2 = true\nrequire(\"vim._core.ui2\").enable({ enable = true, msg = {\n  target = \"msg\",\n} })\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhen entering command mode the statusline should not be seen or moved up as in this case.\n\n<img width=\"691\" height=\"211\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6730dd20-6813-4b26-be81-c6a163df1915\" />\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 25.10\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
